title: Summarise the climate variable by growth stages — climate_by_stages
text: Define growth stages S0: start year emergence S1: emergence flowering time - 300Cd S2: flowering time - 300Cd flowering time + 100Cd S3: flowering time + 100 Cd flowering time + 600Cd S4: flowering + 600Cd maturity Climate variables stage: defination stages n: Number days stage avgt: average temperature (C) sum.tt: total thermal time (Cd) base temperature 0C avg.mint: average minimum temperature avg.maxt: average maximum temperature sum.rain: total rainfall avg.evap: average evapration avg.radn average radiation hot.days: number hot days (daily maximum temperature 30C) .hot.days: number hot days (daily maximum temperature 35C) frost.days: number frost days (daily minimum temperature less 0C) hot.sum: total thermal time 30C hot days (daily maximum temperature 30C) .hot.sum: total thermal time 35C hot days (daily maximum temperature 35C) frost.sum: total thermal time 0C frost days (daily minimum temperature less 0C) vpd: vapour-pressure deficit te: transpiration efficiency bio.radn: bio.radn bio.water: bio.water bio.tt: bio.tt ptq: photothermal quotient avt.diffuse.radn: average diffuse radiation

title: Summarise the climate variable by growth stages — climate_by_stages
code: if (FALSE) {    sowing <- rep(as.Date("1981-05-01"), 10)    emergence <- rep(10, 10)    heading <- NULL    flowering <- runif(10) * 20 + 50    maturity <- runif(10) * 20 + 100    latitude <- -27    res <- climate_by_stages(climates = climates,                              sowing = sowing,                             emergence = emergence,                              heading = heading,                             flowering = flowering,                             maturity = maturity,                             latitude = latitude) }

title: Calculate Dew Point Temperature from Minimum Temperature and Relative Humidity — dp_mint
text: Numeric. Dew point temperature degrees Celsius.

title: Calculate Dew Point Temperature from Minimum Temperature and Relative Humidity — dp_mint
text: dew point temperature calculated using following equations: $$ \gamma = \frac{\cdot T}{b + T} + \ln\left(\frac{RH}{100}\right) $$ $$ T_{dew} = \frac{b \cdot \gamma}{- \gamma} $$ \(= 17.62\) \(b = 243.12\).

title: Hourly Air Temperature Interpolation — tt_hourly_pp
text: Computes hourly estimates air temperature (Ta) daily Tmin, Tmax, day length using method Goudriaan (1994). function assumes sinusoidal temperature variation daylight hours exponential decay sunset.

title: Hourly Air Temperature Interpolation — tt_hourly_pp
code: tt_hourly_pp(tmin, tmax, tmax_b, tmin_a, lat, doy)

title: Hourly Air Temperature Interpolation — tt_hourly_pp
text: tmin Numeric. Minimum temperature day (°C). tmax Numeric. Maximum temperature day (°C). tmax_b Numeric. Maximum temperature previous day (°C). tmin_a Numeric. Minimum temperature following day (°C). lat Numeric. Latitude location (degrees, -90 90). doy Integer. Day year (1 366).

title: Hourly Air Temperature Interpolation — tt_hourly_pp
text: numeric vector length 24 containing estimated hourly air temperatures (°C).

title: Hourly Air Temperature Interpolation — tt_hourly_pp
text: - **Daytime interpolation**: sunlight hours, Ta estimated using sinusoidal curve fitted Tmin Tmax. - **Nighttime interpolation**: sunset, Ta follows exponential decline sunset temperature next morning's Tmin. - **Sunrise Sunset Calculation**:   - Sunrise hour: `hsrise = 12 - d/2`   - Sunset hour: `hsset = 12 + d/2`   - Tmax occurs hour = 13.5. Controlled Environment module used weather data, function takes hourly values instead computing .

title: Hourly Air Temperature Interpolation — tt_hourly_pp
text: Goudriaan, J. (1994). Advanced Methods Calculating Radiation Models.             Netherlands Journal Agricultural Science, 42(4), 315-323.

title: Hourly Air Temperature Interpolation — tt_hourly_pp
code: tmin <- 10 tmax <- 20 tmax_b <- 21 tmin_a <- 11 lat <- -27 doy <- 10 hourly_temps <- tt_hourly_pp(tmin, tmax, tmax_b, tmin_a, lat, doy)
